SIMPLE: insufferable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insufferable
<hw>In*suf"fer*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Incapable of being suffered, borne, or endured; insupportable;
unendurable; intolerable; <as>as, <ex>insufferable</ex> heat, cold, or
pain; <ex>insufferable</ex> wrongs.</as></def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Offensive beyond endurance; detestable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A multitude of scribblers who daily pester the world with their
<qex>insufferable</qex> stuff.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insufferably</ent>⟦br⟧
